Why AGPL-3.0:

Haven OS is licensed under the GNU Affero General Public License v3.0.
This license was chosen deliberately and for specific reasons:

1. Strong copyleft. Any fork or modification of Haven OS must also be
   open source under the same terms. This prevents proprietary forks.

2. The network use clause. Unlike standard GPL, AGPL requires that if
   you run a modified version of Haven OS as a network service, you must
   release your modifications. This closes the "SaaS loophole."

3. Charter alignment. A company that would build surveillance
   infrastructure on top of Haven OS cannot keep those modifications
   private. The license makes the charter's commitments structurally
   harder to violate.

If you want to use Haven OS in a way that the AGPL does not permit,
contact the project maintainers to discuss alternative arrangements.
